# `List` ‚Äî ordered, indexed, allows duplicates

## Two implementations

- **`ArrayList`** ‚Äî resizing array; **O(1)** index access, amortised O(1) append ‚Äî **your default**
- **`LinkedList`** ‚Äî doubly-linked; O(1) at the ends, O(n) random ‚Äî rarely worth it

```java
List<String> names = new ArrayList<>();
names.get(1);           // O(1)
names.set(0, "alex");   // replace at index
names.remove("alex");   // remove first occurrence
```
